					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">One slightly simpler way of doing that:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">;check if B button has just been pressed<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; lda joypad_cur<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; eor joypad_prev<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; and joypad_cur<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; and #BUTTON_B<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; beq notpressed<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &#40;code for when the button is pressed&#41;<br /><br />notpressed:<br /></div>
<br />
<br />An even further simplification is to perform the "(cur XOR prev) AND cur" calculation immediately after reading the button states and caching it - in fact, a vast majority of licensed NES games do exactly this.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
